descript.abstract: This file is a result of first 18-County Atlanta Region Bicycle Facilities Inventory, collected during May-July 2008 by L. Zuyeva for the Atlanta Regional Commission. While this file has been created with input from numerous local jurisdictions and stakeholders, and some facilities were verified through site visits, please be aware that this inventory might not be completely up-to-date. Data was collected for the following counties (and municipalities within them): Barrow, Bartow, Cherokee, Clayton, Cobb, Coweta, DeKalb, Douglas, Fayette, Fulton, Forsyth, Gwinnett, Henry, Newton, Paulding, Rockdale, Spalding and Walton.
descript.purpose: The purpose of this inventory was to see what bicycle facilities are on the ground, and to share this information with local governments, advocates, a the general public. In the future, this inventory could be used to find the critical missing links and to plan for additional bicycle facilities in the Atlanta region.
descript.supplinf: This inventory is intended to be updated on regular basis (bi-annually.)
